│ This is an interesting bug. The `foldSelectEqualityTest` optimization incorrectly simplifies a select chain into an `icmp samesign eq`, leading to a miscompile where a defined `false`  │
│ result becomes `poison`. The core issue is that the transform `(X==C) ? (Y==C) : (X==Y)` into `X==Y` is not valid for `icmp samesign` when `C` is a non-zero constant, because it        │
│ changes the poison semantics.                                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ My initial attempts to fix this were too aggressive, disabling the optimization for all `samesign` cases, which caused regressions. The key insight is that this optimization is only    │
│ valid for `samesign` when the constant `C` is zero. When `C` is non-zero, if `X` equals `C` but `Y` has a different sign, the original logic correctly produces `false`, while the       │
│ transformed `icmp samesign eq` would produce `poison`.                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The correct fix is to refine the existing check. Instead of completely disabling the fold for `samesign`, we should only disable it when the constant `Z` is non-zero. If `Z` is not a   │
│ constant, we should also be conservative and disable the fold, as we cannot determine its value.                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Here is the patch that implements this logic:                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```diff                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp                                                                                                                              │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp                                                                                                                              │
│ @@ -1448,6 +1448,19 @@                                                                                                                                                                   │
│    if (!match(XeqY,                                                                                                                                                                      │
│               m_c_SpecificICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, m_Specific(X), m_Specific(Y))))                                                                                                        │
│      return nullptr;                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ +                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ +  // If we have a samesign comparison, we can't do the fold if the constant                                                                                                             │
│ +  // is non-zero, since that would change the poison conditions.                                                                                                                        │
│ +  if (cast<ICmpInst>(XeqY)->hasSameSign()) {                                                                                                                                            │
│ +    if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Z)) {                                                                                                                                           │
│ +      if (!C->isZero())                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ +        return nullptr;                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ +    } else {                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ +      // If Z is not a constant, we can't analyze the poison behavior change.                                                                                                           │
│ +      // Be conservative and bail out for samesign.                                                                                                                                     │
│ +      return nullptr;                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ +    }                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ +  }                                                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│    return replaceInstUsesWith(Sel, XeqY);                                                                                                                                                │
│  }                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
